<article>
    <h1>PUNCHY PEDAS</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200904/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-04"><time>2020-09-04</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline">Tan Hsueh Yun Food Ed&#xAD;i&#xAD;tor rec&#xAD;om&#xAD;mends</span>
    </section>

    <p>I can­not un­der­stand why a chilli cow­ard like me keeps crav­ing heat and spice. Usu­ally I steer clear, but in the last year or so, my palate has changed in a star­tling way. Now, I crave sam­bal bela­can and have food with lash­ings of chilli.</p>
    <p>While I’m on a hot streak, let me tell you about the As­sam Pedas ($19.90, left) from Blue Spoon, a home-based food busi­ness.</p>
    <p>In­stead of fish or prawns, which over­cook in a heart­beat, it of­fers chicken. The two chicken Mary­lands will not be­come tough and dry even if you re­heat them en­thu­si­as­ti­cally.</p>
    <p>What thrills me is the tangy, zippy gravy. Toma­toes and pineap­ple add to the tart­ness, which my palate also loves. A por­tion is good for two, and I would add fish or prawns to any left­over gravy.</p>
    <p>An­other win­ner is the Beef Stew ($22.90) with a sat­is­fy­ingly thick mushroom gravy. This is pure com­fort food, es­pe­cially on a grey day. My only com­plaint is that freez­ing changes the tex­ture of the car­rots, but at least the potatoes are fine.</p>
    <p>You can­not go wrong with beef or chicken Shep­herd’s Pies, which you can buy in bulk and store in the freezer. They are $8.90 each or $8.50 each if you buy eight or more.</p>
    <p>I am keep­ing my fin­gers crossed that soon, Blue Spoon will sell pouches of the as­sam pedas gravy. I have such grand plans for it.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Blue Spoon OR­DER­ING INFO: To or­der, What­sApp 9147-4678 DE­LIV­ERY: Min­i­mum or­der of $35, and de­liv­ery charges range from $6 to $16 depend­ing on dis­tance</p>
    <p>INFO: Go to @blue­spoonsg on In­sta­gram for menu and or­der­ing in­for­ma­tion</p>

